    <description>Inflorescences dense to diffuse, 21–85 × 2–14 cm, internodes in floral branchlets
        0.7–3 mm. Pedicels 0.9–3 mm. Flowers: hypanthium obconic or subglobose, long
        stipitate-glandular; petals tightly coiled, linear or narrowly lanceolate, 0.1–0.2 mm wide.
        2n = 14.</description>
    <phenology>Flowering Jun–Sep</phenology>
    <habitat> Shaded rocks and ledges, granite, gneiss, or acidic humus over limestone or shallow
        rocky soil</habitat>
    <elevation> 100–2000 m</elevation>
